    <item>
      <title>Unique Obstacles For Asian Americans In Voting</title>
      <description>There's been a lot of attention on how voter ID laws might affect minority groups like African-Americans and Latinos. But some observers say that Asian Americans may also be affected. Host Michel Martin discusses the potential impact with Glenn Magpantay of the Asian American Legal Defense and Education Fund.</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Sep 2012 12:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414284/unique-obstacles-for-asian-americans-in-voting?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414284/unique-obstacles-for-asian-americans-in-voting?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There's been a lot of attention on how voter ID laws might affect minority groups like African-Americans and Latinos. But some observers say that Asian Americans may also be affected. Host Michel Martin discusses the potential impact with Glenn Magpantay of the Asian American Legal Defense and Education Fund.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161414284">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161414284">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>House Democrats Offer Their Solution For Voter ID</title>
      <description>Democratic members of the House introduced a bill yesterday that would allow voters without ID to sign an affidavit attesting to their identity at the polls. The new bill is the latest in the ongoing voter ID debate and host Michel Martin speaks with one of the bill's sponsors Congressman Rick Larsen about the proposal.</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Sep 2012 12:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414286/house-democrats-offer-their-solution-for-voter-id?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414286/house-democrats-offer-their-solution-for-voter-id?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Democratic members of the House introduced a bill yesterday that would allow voters without ID to sign an affidavit attesting to their identity at the polls. The new bill is the latest in the ongoing voter ID debate and host Michel Martin speaks with one of the bill's sponsors Congressman Rick Larsen about the proposal.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161414286">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161414286">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>'Bleak' Picture For Minority Managers In Newsroom</title>
      <description>A new study shows media has a lot of influence on attitudes about Latinos. But when it comes to who decides what Americans see on TV or news, the National Association of Black Journalists says minorities have a long way to go. Host Michel Martin speaks with NABJ's Bob Butler and Felix Sanchez of the National Hispanic Foundation for the Arts.</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Sep 2012 12:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414290/bleak-picture-for-minority-managers-in-newsroom?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/19/161414290/bleak-picture-for-minority-managers-in-newsroom?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A new study shows media has a lot of influence on attitudes about Latinos. But when it comes to who decides what Americans see on TV or news, the National Association of Black Journalists says minorities have a long way to go. Host Michel Martin speaks with NABJ's Bob Butler and Felix Sanchez of the National Hispanic Foundation for the Arts.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161414290">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161414290">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://ad.doubleclick.net/jump/n6735.NPR/news_u_s_;sz=300x80;ord=2027103309"><img alt="" src="http://ad.doubleclick.net/ad/n6735.NPR/news_u_s_;sz=300x80;ord=2027103309"/></a>]]></content:encoded>
