    <item>
      <title>McRib Fans May Have To Wait Till Christmas For Their Sandwich Fix</title>
      <description>Fans complain as McDonald's delays this year's pork-a-licious McRib sandwich to boost an anticipated slump in winter sales. The sandwich is a food engineering marvel of pork trimmings pressed into a boneless rib shape, topped with pickles and barbecue sauce, sandwiched on a bun.</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Sep 2012 11:10:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2012/09/19/161403177/mcrib-fans-may-have-to-wait-till-christmas-for-their-sandwich-fix?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2012/09/19/161403177/mcrib-fans-may-have-to-wait-till-christmas-for-their-sandwich-fix?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Fans complain as McDonald's delays this year's pork-a-licious McRib sandwich to boost an anticipated slump in winter sales. The sandwich is a food engineering marvel of pork trimmings pressed into a boneless rib shape, topped with pickles and barbecue sauce, sandwiched on a bun.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161403177">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161403177">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
