    <item>
      <title>Chicago Teachers Union Delegates Vote To End Strike</title>
      <description>The Chicago Teachers Union called off its strike today. On Sunday the delegates voted down a proposed contract offer, saying they needed more time to consider it. Classes are scheduled to resume on Wednesday. Claudio Sanchez talks to Audie Cornish.</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Sep 2012 18:29:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/18/161376031/chicago-teachers-union-delegates-vote-to-end-strike?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/18/161376031/chicago-teachers-union-delegates-vote-to-end-strike?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Chicago Teachers Union called off its strike today. On Sunday the delegates voted down a proposed contract offer, saying they needed more time to consider it. Classes are scheduled to resume on Wednesday. Claudio Sanchez talks to Audie Cornish.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161376031">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161376031">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
