    <item>
      <title>Romney Still Doing Damage Control For '47 Percent'</title>
      <description>Anytime a candidate calls an unexpected press conference in the evening, you know it's not good news. We look at the latest news and political fall out from the release of Mitt Romney's remarks at a private fundraiser. The comments were made in May and the recording was released by &lt;em&gt;Mother Jones&lt;/em&gt; magazine.</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Sep 2012 15:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/18/161369274/romney-still-doing-damage-control-for-47-percent?ft=1&amp;f=1003</link>
      <guid>http://www.npr.org/2012/09/18/161369274/romney-still-doing-damage-control-for-47-percent?ft=1&amp;f=1003</guid>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Anytime a candidate calls an unexpected press conference in the evening, you know it's not good news. We look at the latest news and political fall out from the release of Mitt Romney's remarks at a private fundraiser. The comments were made in May and the recording was released by <em>Mother Jones</em> magazine.</p><p><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/email/emailAFriend.php?storyId=161369274">&raquo; E-Mail This</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="http://del.icio.us/post?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Ftemplates%2Fstory%2Fstory.php%3FstoryId%3D161369274">&raquo; Add to Del.icio.us</a></p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://ad.doubleclick.net/jump/n6735.NPR/news_u_s_;sz=300x80;ord=1339223434"><img alt="" src="http://ad.doubleclick.net/ad/n6735.NPR/news_u_s_;sz=300x80;ord=1339223434"/></a>]]></content:encoded>
